.TH MDE-MIGRATE-FROM-1X 1 "2026-05-19" "MDE 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mde-migrate-from-1x \- atomic config-path migrator for the v1.x → v2.0.0 rebrand
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mde-migrate-from-1x
.SH DESCRIPTION
For each of the three locked
.RI ( legacy ", " target )
pairs:
.IP \(bu 2
.I ~/.config/mackes-shell/
\(->
.I ~/.config/mde/
.IP \(bu 2
.I ~/.cache/mackes/
\(->
.I ~/.cache/mde/
.IP \(bu 2
.I ~/.local/state/mackes/
\(->
.I ~/.local/state/mde/
.P
If the legacy path exists and the target does not,
.B mde-migrate-from-1x
atomically moves the legacy tree (via
.BR os.replace (3)
when source + target share a filesystem; falls back to recursive
copy + delete cross-FS). Idempotent: re-running on an
already-migrated box is a no-op exit 0.
.SH OUTPUT
Logged via
.B systemd-cat -t mde-migrate
with stderr fallback. Each step reports `moved` / `noop` /
`collision` / `failed`.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B mde-shell-migrate-v2(1),
.B mde-session(1)
